data.description: Endearing intown cottage perched on a stately corner lot of historic Elberton. A town  mulled in history, the slow days of yesteryear are easy to imagine while you sip sweet tea rocking on the front porch. Soaring ceilings and a grand hall entrance make a great first impression. 12 foot ceilings throughout make every room feel open and airy while large bright windows allow light to dance all around. French doors open into the sweetest cottage kitchen where you'll never be left in want. Cabinets are smartly laid out with not an inch wasted! The spacious laundry room is conveniently located off the kitchen without getting in the way and the flow of the home is easy living.   This city corner lot offers a lot of privacy tucked in behind a full privacy fence. Off street parking is easily accessed where you will enter the home through the laundry + mud room. Large grilling deck, attractive landscaping and lots of space offer endless opportunity for entertaining or enjoying the slow life. Watch the grass grow sitting on the bench swing while Fido hangs out in the picket dog yard. This is a great home to watch the world hurry by.
